    rdfs:comment "\\(\\LARGE F = p \\cdot n \\cdot \\Delta A\\) In the limit of infinitely small sections, this gives the integral of the pressure times the area around the closed surface. Using the symbol S dA for integration, we have: \\(\\LARGE F = \\int_S (p \\, \\mathbf{n}) \\, dA\\) where the integral is taken all around the body. On the figure, that is why the integral si" .

