    rdfs:comment "(For supersonic airfoils, the aerodynamic center is nearer the 1/2 chord location.) When computing the trim of an aircraft, model rocket, or kite, we usually apply the aerodynamic forces at the aerodynamic center of airfoils and compute the center of pressure of the vehicle as an area-weighted average of the centers of the components." .

