    rdfs:comment "We can determine the value of the mass flow rate from the flow conditions." .

:Evidence_nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate_structure_aware_large_s01_c00_kg00_0c69eaf646 a :Cl_Evidence ;
    dcterms:bibliographicCitation "page=1; section=page-1; chunk_id=nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate-structure_aware_large-s01-c00" ;
    dcterms:conformsTo "confidence=0.500" ;
    dcterms:source "nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate" ;
    rdfs:comment "Mass Flow Rate If the fluid initially passes through an area A at velocity V , we can define a volume of mass to be swept out in some amount of time t . The volume v is: \\(\\LARGE v=AVt\\) A units check gives area x length/time x time = area x length = volume. The mass m contained in this volume is simply density rho ( \\(\\bf\\rho\\) ) times the volume." .

:Evidence_nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate_structure_aware_large_s01_c00_kg01_5c85206c44 a :Cl_Evidence ;
