    dcterms:source "nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate" ;
    rdfs:comment "From Newton’s Second Law of Motion , the aerodynamic forces on an aircraft ( lift and drag ) are directly related to the change in momentum of a gas with time." .

:Evidence_nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate_structure_aware_large_s02_c00_kg06_a138579eb6 a :Cl_Evidence ;
    dcterms:bibliographicCitation "page=2; section=page-2; chunk_id=nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate-structure_aware_large-s02-c00" ;
    dcterms:conformsTo "confidence=0.500" ;
    dcterms:source "nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate" ;
    rdfs:comment "From Newton’s Second Law of Motion , the aerodynamic forces on an aircraft ( lift and drag ) are directly related to the change in momentum of a gas with time." .

:Evidence_nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate_structure_aware_large_s02_c00_kg07_a374d5e538 a :Cl_Evidence ;
    dcterms:bibliographicCitation "page=2; section=page-2; chunk_id=nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate-structure_aware_large-s02-c00" ;
    dcterms:conformsTo "confidence=0.500" ;
    dcterms:source "nasa_bga_mass_flow_rate" ;
    rdfs:comment "The momentum is defined to be the mass times the velocity, so we would expect the aerodynamic forces to depend on the mass flow rate past an object." .

:Evidence_nasa_bga_spcal_structure_aware_large_s00_c00_kg00_f506b74d8b a :Cl_Evidence ;
    dcterms:bibliographicCitation "page=0; section=page-0; chunk_id=nasa_bga_spcal-structure_aware_large-s00-c00" ;
    dcterms:conformsTo "confidence=0.500" ;
    dcterms:source "nasa_bga_spcal" ;
    rdfs:comment "Aerodynamic Forces As an object moves through the atmosphere, the gas molecules of the atmosphere near the object are disturbed and move around the object. Aerodynamic forces are generated between the gas and the object. The magnitude of these forces depends on the shape of the object, the speed of the object, the mass of the gas going by the objec" .

:Evidence_nasa_bga_spcal_structure_aware_large_s00_c00_kg01_99c1fe6ba8 a :Cl_Evidence ;
    dcterms:bibliographicCitation "page=0; section=page-0; chunk_id=nasa_bga_spcal-structure_aware_large-s00-c00" ;
    dcterms:conformsTo "confidence=0.500" ;
    dcterms:source "nasa_bga_spcal" ;
    rdfs:comment "Representative values for the properties of air are given on another page, but the actual value of the parameter depends on the state of the gas and the altitude ." .

